{"word":"διψάω","slug":"διψάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>διψάω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:δίψα'><el>δίψα</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to thirst</i>, <el>διψάων [ᾱ]</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; of the ground, <i>to be thirsty, parched</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to thirst after</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>: later <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to long</i> to do, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}